Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "ludak":

1. *Ludak* je trčao ulicom i vikao na sav glas. (The *lunatic* was running down the street and shouting at the top of his lungs.)
2. Drago mi je da je moj prijatelj *ludak* jer uvek me nasmeje. (I'm glad my friend is a *crazy person* because he always makes me laugh.)
3. Šta se dešava s ovim *ludakom*? (What's going on with this *madman*?)
4. On je *ludak* ako misli da može da pobedi u ovoj trci. (He's a *fool* if he thinks he can win this race.)
5. *Ludak* je mislio da će skočiti s krova i preživeti. (The *madman* thought he could jump off the roof and survive.)

Note: The word "ludak" can have different translations in English depending on the context in which it is used.